               <head>Grant; Bury St Edmunds (?); c. 1220-30</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> <supplied><placeName key="place_104540">Bury St Edmunds (?)</placeName></supplied>
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> de la <surname>Care</surname>, the prior</persName>, 
                  and brethren of the <orgName key="org_105023">hospital of St. Nicholas without the east gate of St. Edmund</orgName>, 
                  grant and quitclaim to the brethren of the
                  <orgName key="org_105024">hospital of St. Peter</orgName> all their right in a fourth part of one acre of arable land
                  called 'Holdefader acre' lying at <placeName type="minor">Dristnapes</placeName>, which they had by the gift of 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> de <surname>Canter</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_104540">Bury St Edmunds (St. Eadmund)</placeName></persName>; 
                  for this grant the said brethren of St. Peter gave 6s. of silver. 
                  (<origDate notBefore="1220" notAfter="1230" precision="low">c. 1220-30</origDate>.) 
                  Witn. <persName>
                           <forename>Stephen</forename> alderman of <placeName role="person" key="place_104540">Bury St Edmunds (St. Eadmund)</placeName></persName>, 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Martyn</forename> de <surname>Bertune</surname> provost</persName>, etc. 
                  </p>
                  </msItem>
